entry.content:
Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Frances "the Shape" Vorne (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a photograph of Frances "the Shape" Vorne wearing a swimsuit made from remnants of a captured Nazi parachute (pictured) was one of the most sought-after pin-ups of World War II?

entry.content: ... that the play-by-email game Blood Pit was so complex that even its programmer had trouble winning?

entry.title: José Cobo Cano (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that José Cobo Cano compared officiating same-sex marriages to celebrating the Eucharist with Coca-Cola?

entry.title: Eternal Blue (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Eternal Blue, a metalcore album, was inspired in part by 1980s pop music?

entry.title: Maisi (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Loud LDN co-founder Maisi came joint last in the 2022 Maldon mud race, behind a naked runner who had been forced to start after everyone else?

entry.title: 1976 Spring Hill shooting (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the perpetrator of the 1976 Spring Hill shooting allegedly committed the attack in a rage after being denied membership to a model plane club?

entry.title: Wendy McMahon (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that CBS News and Stations president Wendy McMahon helped bring local evening news back to the network's Detroit station after 20 years?
